iOS-Scroll-Views

Illustrates managing scroll views for various purposes created totally programmatically.

The user will find 4 examples:

- a scroll view for a very large image using 2 gesture recognizers for zooming in and out;

- a scroll view for a complex view hierarchy;

- scrolling through multiple pages of content;

- «peeking» scrolling through that gives a glimpse of the previous / next page as well as the current page.